<html><head><meta http-equiv="Content-Type" content="text/html; charset=utf-8" /><meta http-equiv="Content-Style-Type" content="text/css" /><meta name="generator" content="Aspose.Words for .NET 13.4.0.0" /><title>Written evidence from the National Union of Rail, Maritime and Transport Workers (RMT) (HCS0015)</title></head><body><div><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:10pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="font-size:10pt; line-height:115%; margin:0pt 0pt 10pt; text-align:center"><span style="font-family:Tahoma; font-size:10pt">Written evidence from the National Union of Rail, Maritime and Transport Workers (RMT) (HCS0015)</span></p><h2 style="font-size:10pt; font-weight:normal; line-height:150%; margin:0pt; page-break-after:avoid; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:Tahoma; font-size:10pt; font-weight:bold">&#xa0;</span></h2><h2 style="font-size:10pt; font-weight:normal; line-height:150%; margin:0pt; page-break-after:avoid; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:Tahoma; font-size:10pt; font-weight:bold; text-decoration:underline">Introduction</span></h2><p style="font-size:10pt; line-height:115%; margin:0pt 0pt 10pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:Tahoma; font-size:10pt">The National Union of Rail, Maritime and Transport Workers (RMT) welcome the opportunity to submit </span><span style="font-family:Tahoma; font-size:10pt">our views as part of TRANSCOM’s inquiry into the Government’s maritime policy</span><span style="font-family:Tahoma; font-size:10pt"> strategy</span><span style="font-family:Tahoma; font-size:10pt">.</span></p><p style="font-size:10pt; line-height:115%; margin:0pt 0pt 10pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:Tahoma; font-size:10pt">The RMT </span><span style="font-family:Tahoma; font-size:10pt">organises</span><span style="font-family:Tahoma; font-size:10pt"> </span><span style="font-family:Tahoma; font-size:10pt">around 7</span><span style="font-family:Tahoma; font-size:10pt">,000 </span><span style="font-family:Tahoma; font-size:10pt">offshore workers, including</span><span style="font-family:Tahoma; font-size:10pt"> d</span><span style="font-family:Tahoma; font-size:10pt">rilling, engineering/maintenance, diver, </span><span style="font-family:Tahoma; font-size:10pt">and catering grades</span><span style="font-family:Tahoma; font-size:10pt">,</span><span style="font-family:Tahoma; font-size:10pt"> </span><span style="font-family:Tahoma; font-size:10pt">and </span><span style="font-family:Tahoma; font-size:10pt">all of these workers </span><span style="font-family:Tahoma; font-size:10pt">require helicopter </span><span style="font-family:Tahoma; font-size:10pt">transport to and from installations on the UK Continental Shelf</span><span style="font-family:Tahoma; font-size:10pt"> a</span><span style="font-family:Tahoma; font-size:10pt">t the start and end of their 2 or 3</span><span style="font-family:Tahoma; font-size:10pt"> week long tours</span><span style="font-family:Tahoma; font-size:10pt">.</span></p><p style="font-size:10pt; line-height:150%; margin:0pt 0pt 10pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:Tahoma; font-size:10pt; font-weight:bold">Key Points</span></p><ul type="disc" style="margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt"><li style="font-family:Symbol; font-size:10pt; line-height:150%; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 27.6pt; padding-left:8.4pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:Tahoma; font-size:10pt; font-weight:bold">Public Inquiry</span><span style="font-family:Tahoma; font-size:10pt; font-weight:bold"> </span><span style="font-family:Tahoma; font-size:10pt">–</span><span style="font-family:Tahoma; font-size:10pt"> </span><span style="font-family:Tahoma; font-size:10pt">RMT support a </span><span style="font-family:Tahoma; font-size:10pt">Cullen-style</span><span style="font-family:Tahoma; font-size:10pt"> public inquiry into helicopter safety, partly in order to address the offshore work</span><span style="font-family:Tahoma; font-size:10pt">er’s chronic lack of confidence in helicopter transport. </span></li><li style="font-family:Symbol; font-size:10pt; line-height:150%; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 27.6pt; padding-left:8.4pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:Tahoma; font-size:10pt; font-weight:bold">Adoption of </span><span style="font-family:Tahoma; font-size:10pt; font-weight:bold">best practice </span><span style="font-family:Tahoma; font-size:10pt; font-weight:bold">standards</span><span style="font-family:Tahoma; font-size:10pt; font-weight:bold"> </span><span style="font-family:Tahoma; font-size:10pt">–</span><span style="font-family:Tahoma; font-size:10pt"> </span><span style="font-family:Tahoma; font-size:10pt">The safety record of</span><span style="font-family:Tahoma; font-size:10pt"> offshore helicopter</span><span style="font-family:Tahoma; font-size:10pt">s</span><span style="font-family:Tahoma; font-size:10pt"> ha</span><span style="font-family:Tahoma; font-size:10pt">s</span><span style="font-family:Tahoma; font-size:10pt"> </span><span style="font-family:Tahoma; font-size:10pt">worsened in the last decade, yet some operators have considerably better safety records than others. The highest </span><span style="font-family:Tahoma; font-size:10pt">standards,</span><span style="font-family:Tahoma; font-size:10pt"> particularly in pilot training</span><span style="font-family:Tahoma; font-size:10pt"> and operating procedures</span><span style="font-family:Tahoma; font-size:10pt">,</span><span style="font-family:Tahoma; font-size:10pt"> as exist in the Norwegian sector should be adopted across the</span><span style="font-family:Tahoma; font-size:10pt"> UK offshore</span><span style="font-family:Tahoma; font-size:10pt"> helicopter industry.</span><span style="font-family:Tahoma; font-size:10pt"> </span><span style="font-family:Tahoma; font-size:10pt">Trade union access to the workforce, at heliports and on installations, should be legislated </span><span style="font-family:Tahoma; font-size:10pt">for, if necessary.</span></li><li style="font-family:Symbol; font-size:10pt; line-height:150%; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 27.6pt; padding-left:8.4pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:Tahoma; font-size:10pt; font-weight:bold">Role of domestic regulator</span><span style="font-family:Tahoma; font-size:10pt; font-weight:bold"> </span><span style="font-family:Tahoma; font-size:10pt">– The proposal to increase the role of the European Aviation Safety Agency (EASA) in regulating the </span><span style="font-family:Tahoma; font-size:10pt">UK </span><span style="font-family:Tahoma; font-size:10pt">offshore helicopter industry </span><span style="font-family:Tahoma; font-size:10pt">combined with cuts to the</span><span style="font-family:Tahoma; font-size:10pt"> </span><span style="font-family:Tahoma; font-size:10pt">Civil Aviation Authority </span><span style="font-family:Tahoma; font-size:10pt">threatens the effectiveness</span><span style="font-family:Tahoma; font-size:10pt"> of the</span><span style="font-family:Tahoma; font-size:10pt"> UK</span><span style="font-family:Tahoma; font-size:10pt"> regulatory framework</span><span style="font-family:Tahoma; font-size:10pt">.</span><span style="font-family:Tahoma; font-size:10pt"> </span></li><li style="font-family:Symbol; font-size:10pt; line-height:150%; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 27.6pt; padding-left:8.4pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:Tahoma; font-size:10pt; font-weight:bold">Helicopter fleet </span><span style="font-family:Tahoma; font-size:10pt">–</span><span style="font-family:Tahoma; font-size:10pt"> We are concerned that t</span><span style="font-family:Tahoma; font-size:10pt">he </span><span style="font-family:Tahoma; font-size:10pt">Government’s statistical records </span><span style="font-family:Tahoma; font-size:10pt">of the number of passengers and models providing helicopter transport for the offshore workforce are inaccurate.</span><span style="font-family:Tahoma; font-size:10pt"> This is not helpful when workers’ confidence in the helicopter fleet has been so badly shaken.</span></li><li style="font-family:Symbol; font-size:10pt; line-height:150%; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 27.6pt; padding-left:8.4pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:Tahoma; font-size:10pt; font-weight:bold">Access to justice</span><span style="font-family:Tahoma; font-size:10pt; font-weight:bold"> </span><span style="font-family:Tahoma; font-size:10pt">– Whilst a devolved matter, serious consideration should be given to supporting moves in the Scottish Parliament to reform the fatal accident </span><span style="font-family:Tahoma; font-size:10pt">inquiry process which, at present compounds the grief of families affected by fatal offshore helicopter accidents.</span><span style="font-family:Tahoma; font-size:10pt"> </span></li></ul><p style="font-size:10pt; line-height:150%; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 36pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:Tahoma; font-size:10pt">&#xa0;</span></p><ol type="1" style="margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt"><li style="font-family:Tahoma; font-size:10pt; font-weight:bold; line-height:150%; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 14.49pt; padding-left:6.81pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:Tahoma; font-size:10pt; font-weight:bold; text-decoration:underline">Public Inquiry</span><span style="font-family:Tahoma; font-size:10pt"> </span></li></ol><p style="font-size:10pt; line-height:150%; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 21.3pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:-21.3pt"><span style="font-family:Tahoma; font-size:10pt; font-weight:bold">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="font-size:10pt; line-height:150%; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 21.3pt; text-indent:-21.3pt"><span style="font-family:Tahoma; font-size:10pt">1.1 </span><span style="font-family:Tahoma; font-size:10pt">              </span><span style="font-family:Tahoma; font-size:10pt">The offshore unions, RMT, Nautilus, Unite, Balpa and GMB are</span><span style="font-family:Tahoma; font-size:10pt"> calling </span><span style="font-family:Tahoma; font-size:10pt">for </span><span style="font-family:Tahoma; font-size:10pt">a public inquiry into </span><span style="font-family:Tahoma; font-size:10pt">the safety</span><span style="font-family:Tahoma; font-size:10pt"> off</span><span style="font-family:Tahoma; font-size:10pt"> </span><span style="font-family:Tahoma; font-size:10pt">helicop</span><span style="font-family:Tahoma; font-size:10pt">ter transport</span><span style="font-family:Tahoma; font-size:10pt"> in the</span><span style="font-family:Tahoma; font-size:10pt"> offshore</span><span style="font-family:Tahoma; font-size:10pt"> industry</span><span style="font-family:Tahoma; font-size:10pt"> which would cover</span><span style="font-family:Tahoma; font-size:10pt">:</span><span style="font-family:Tahoma; font-size:10pt"> </span></p><ul type="disc" style="margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt"><li style="font-family:Symbol; font-size:10pt; line-height:115%; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 20.5pt; padding-left:8.4pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:Tahoma; font-size:10pt">Comparison </span><span style="font-family:Tahoma; font-size:10pt">of</span><span style="font-family:Tahoma; font-size:10pt"> </span><span style="font-family:Tahoma; font-size:10pt">the </span><span style="font-family:Tahoma; font-size:10pt">UK </span><span style="font-family:Tahoma; font-size:10pt">safety record and standards of helicopter companies </span><span style="font-family:Tahoma; font-size:10pt">with their counterparts in</span><span style="font-family:Tahoma; font-size:10pt"> the Norwegian sector of the North Sea.</span></li><li style="font-family:Symbol; font-size:10pt; line-height:115%; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 20.5pt; padding-left:8.4pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:Tahoma; font-size:10pt">Trade union access to berths on helicopters</span><span style="font-family:Tahoma; font-size:10pt">.</span></li><li style="font-family:Symbol; font-size:10pt; line-height:115%; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 20.5pt; padding-left:8.4pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:Tahoma; font-size:10pt">The extent and effectiveness of training requirements for helicopter pilots.</span></li><li style="font-family:Symbol; font-size:10pt; line-height:115%; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 20.5pt; padding-left:8.4pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:Tahoma; font-size:10pt">All operational aspects of helicopter transport, from maintenance regimes through to survivability.</span><span style="font-family:Tahoma; font-size:10pt"> </span></li></ul><p style="font-size:10pt; line-height:115%; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 21.3pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:-21.3pt"><span style="font-family:Tahoma; font-size:10pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="font-size:10pt; line-height:115%; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 21.3pt; text-indent:-21.3pt"><span style="font-family:Tahoma; font-size:10pt">1.2</span><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'">&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; </span><span style="font-family:Tahoma; font-size:10pt">Since 1980 there have been nine fatal accidents involving helicopters operati</span><span style="font-family:Tahoma; font-size:10pt">ng in the offshore oil and gas industry, claiming the lives of 114 offshore workers and helicopter crew. There were 44 reportable non-fatal helicopter incidents in the offshore sector over this period.</span></p><p style="font-size:10pt; line-height:115%; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 21.3pt; text-indent:-21.3pt"><span style="font-family:Tahoma; font-size:10pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="font-size:10pt; line-height:115%; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 21.3pt; text-indent:-21.3pt"><span style="font-family:Tahoma; font-size:10pt">1.3</span><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'">&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; </span><span style="font-family:Tahoma; font-size:10pt">It is 25 years since the Piper Alpha disaster in the </span><span style="font-family:Tahoma; font-size:10pt">North Sea and 23 years since the publication of the Cullen Report which was a watershed moment for operational </span><span style="font-family:Tahoma; font-size:10pt">safety</span><span style="font-family:Tahoma; font-size:10pt"> in the offshore oil and gas industry. </span><span style="font-family:Tahoma; font-size:10pt">Key amongst Cullen’s 106</span><span style="font-family:Tahoma; font-size:10pt"> recommendations (all of which were accepted by the Government of the day an</span><span style="font-family:Tahoma; font-size:10pt">d industry) </span><span style="font-family:Tahoma; font-size:10pt">was to institute a safety culture of ‘continuous improvement’ in the offshore industry. </span><span style="font-family:Tahoma; font-size:10pt">We believe that this culture of continuous improvement is critical to improving the safety record of offshore helicopter operations. </span></p><p style="font-size:10pt; line-height:115%; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 21.3pt; text-indent:-21.3pt"><span style="font-family:Tahoma; font-size:10pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="font-size:10pt; line-height:115%; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 21.3pt; text-indent:-21.3pt"><span style="font-family:Tahoma; font-size:10pt">1.4</span><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'">&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; </span><span style="font-family:Tahoma; font-size:10pt">The cost of such an </span><span style="font-family:Tahoma; font-size:10pt">inquiry would not be prohibitive, given the scale of the industry’s annual contribution to</span><span style="font-family:Tahoma; font-size:10pt"> national tax revenue (</span><span style="font-family:Tahoma; font-size:10pt">£10.6 billion in 2011-12</span><a name="_ftnref1"></a><a href="#_ftn1">[1]</a><span style="font-family:Tahoma; font-size:10pt">). </span><span style="font-family:Tahoma; font-size:10pt">For example,</span><span style="font-family:Tahoma; font-size:10pt"> the House of Commons Library recently estimated that the </span><span style="font-family:Tahoma; font-size:10pt">full </span><span style="font-family:Tahoma; font-size:10pt">cost of the Cullen Inquiry in today’s pr</span><span style="font-family:Tahoma; font-size:10pt">ices would be £5.7m</span><a name="_ftnref2"></a><a href="#_ftn2">[2]</a><span style="font-family:Tahoma; font-size:10pt">. </span></p><p style="font-size:10pt; line-height:115%; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 21.3pt; text-indent:-21.3pt"><span style="font-family:Tahoma; font-size:10pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="font-size:10pt; line-height:115%; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 21.3pt; text-indent:-21.3pt"><span style="font-family:Tahoma; font-size:10pt">1.5</span><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'">&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; </span><span style="font-family:Tahoma; font-size:10pt">In the wake of the Clutha bar tragedy in Glasgow</span><span style="font-family:Tahoma; font-size:10pt"> on 29</span><span style="font-family:Tahoma; font-size:6.67pt; vertical-align:super">th</span><span style="font-family:Tahoma; font-size:10pt"> November this year</span><span style="font-family:Tahoma; font-size:10pt">, RMT also accept that there is a serious case for a full public inquiry into all aspects of helicopter transport</span><span style="font-family:Tahoma; font-size:10pt"> </span><span style="font-family:Tahoma; font-size:10pt">covering operations </span><span style="font-family:Tahoma; font-size:10pt">beyond the offshore </span><span style="font-family:Tahoma; font-size:10pt">sector</span><span style="font-family:Tahoma; font-size:10pt">, including</span><span style="font-family:Tahoma; font-size:10pt"> police, air ambulan</span><span style="font-family:Tahoma; font-size:10pt">ce and air-sea rescue</span><span style="font-family:Tahoma; font-size:10pt">.</span></p><p style="font-size:10pt; line-height:115%; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 21.3pt; text-indent:-21.3pt"><span style="font-family:Tahoma; font-size:10pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="font-size:10pt; line-height:115%; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 21.3pt; text-indent:-21.3pt"><span style="font-family:Tahoma; font-size:10pt">1.6</span><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'">&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; </span><span style="font-family:Tahoma; font-size:10pt">It is notable that the</span><span style="font-family:Tahoma; font-size:10pt"> model of helicopter, EC</span><span style="font-family:Tahoma; font-size:10pt"> 135, involved in the </span><span style="font-family:Tahoma; font-size:10pt">Clutha Vaults incident is a Eurocopter</span><span style="font-family:Tahoma; font-size:10pt"> manufactured machine</span><span style="font-family:Tahoma; font-size:10pt">. The models of helicopter that transport the vast majority of offsh</span><span style="font-family:Tahoma; font-size:10pt">ore workers, the EC225 Super Puma and AS332 L, L1 and L2 are all Eurocopter models.</span></p><p style="font-size:10pt; line-height:115%; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 21.3pt; text-indent:-21.3pt"><span style="font-family:Tahoma; font-size:10pt">&#xa0;</span></p><ol start="2" type="1" style="margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt"><li style="font-family:Tahoma; font-size:10pt; font-weight:bold; line-height:115%; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 14.49pt; padding-left:6.81pt; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:Tahoma; font-size:10pt; font-weight:bold">Adoption of </span><span style="font-family:Tahoma; font-size:10pt; font-weight:bold">best practice</span><span style="font-family:Tahoma; font-size:10pt; font-weight:bold"> in helicopter safety</span><span style="font-family:Tahoma; font-size:10pt; font-weight:bold"> standards</span></li></ol><p style="font-size:10pt; line-height:115%; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 21.3pt; text-indent:-21.3pt"><span style="font-family:Tahoma; font-size:10pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="font-size:10pt; line-height:115%; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 21.3pt; text-indent:-21.3pt"><span style="font-family:Tahoma; font-size:10pt">2.2</span><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'">&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; </span><span style="font-family:Tahoma; font-size:10pt">The </span><span style="font-family:Tahoma; font-size:10pt">five incidents, two of them fatal, involving helicopters in the North Sea since February 2009 should press th</span><span style="font-family:Tahoma; font-size:10pt">e Government into concerted and effective action to improve the </span><span style="font-family:Tahoma; font-size:10pt">safety record of helicopter </span><span style="font-family:Tahoma; font-size:10pt">operators</span><span style="font-family:Tahoma; font-size:10pt"> and their operations</span><span style="font-family:Tahoma; font-size:10pt"> in the UK Continental Shelf. Yet the current approach is purely reactive, in terms of the Air Accident Investigation Branch and Civil</span><span style="font-family:Tahoma; font-size:10pt"> Aviation Authority reports, as demonstrated in response to the fatal accident involving a Eurocopter AS332 L2 on 23</span><span style="font-family:Tahoma; font-size:6.67pt; vertical-align:super">rd</span><span style="font-family:Tahoma; font-size:10pt"> August this year which claimed the lives of four offshore workers. </span></p><p style="font-size:10pt; line-height:115%; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 21.3pt; text-indent:-21.3pt"><span style="font-family:Tahoma; font-size:10pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="font-size:10pt; line-height:115%; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 21.3pt; text-indent:-21.3pt"><span style="font-family:Tahoma; font-size:10pt">2.3</span><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'">&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; </span><span style="font-family:Tahoma; font-size:10pt">RMT</span><span style="font-family:Tahoma; font-size:10pt"> is concerned at the variation i</span><span style="font-family:Tahoma; font-size:10pt">n practice that exists amongst he</span><span style="font-family:Tahoma; font-size:10pt">licopter companies operating in the North Sea</span><span style="font-family:Tahoma; font-size:10pt"> and the potential consequences of this in terms of the safety of offshore oil and gas workers</span><span style="font-family:Tahoma; font-size:10pt">. For example, Bristow Helicopters operate to a "gold standard"</span><span style="font-family:Tahoma; font-size:10pt">,</span><span style="font-family:Tahoma; font-size:10pt"> essentially the set of standards applied in the Norwegian sector </span><span style="font-family:Tahoma; font-size:10pt">which are widely acknowledged</span><span style="font-family:Tahoma; font-size:10pt"> as more robust than those in place for the UK sector. </span></p><p style="font-size:10pt; line-height:115%; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 21.3pt; text-indent:-21.3pt"><span style="font-family:Tahoma; font-size:10pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="font-size:10pt; line-height:115%; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 21.3pt; text-indent:-21.3pt"><span style="font-family:Tahoma; font-size:10pt">2.4</span><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'">&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; </span><span style="font-family:Tahoma; font-size:10pt">If</span><span style="font-family:Tahoma; font-size:10pt"> the “gold standard” in inspection, </span><span style="font-family:Tahoma; font-size:10pt">operating procedures, </span><span style="font-family:Tahoma; font-size:10pt">training and maintenance in operation at Bri</span><span style="font-family:Tahoma; font-size:10pt">stow and in the Norwegian sector had been in place in the UK sector,</span><span style="font-family:Tahoma; font-size:10pt"> </span><span style="font-family:Tahoma; font-size:10pt">we believe that </span><span style="font-family:Tahoma; font-size:10pt">four </span><span style="font-family:Tahoma; font-size:10pt">out </span><span style="font-family:Tahoma; font-size:10pt">of the five incidents </span><span style="font-family:Tahoma; font-size:10pt">since February 2009 </span><span style="font-family:Tahoma; font-size:10pt">potentially could </span><span style="font-family:Tahoma; font-size:10pt">have been avoided</span><span style="font-family:Tahoma; font-size:10pt">, including the fatal incidents on 1</span><span style="font-family:Tahoma; font-size:6.67pt; vertical-align:super">st</span><span style="font-family:Tahoma; font-size:10pt"> April 2009 and 23</span><span style="font-family:Tahoma; font-size:6.67pt; vertical-align:super">rd</span><span style="font-family:Tahoma; font-size:10pt"> August 2013 which claimed </span><span style="font-family:Tahoma; font-size:10pt">a total of 20 lives</span><span style="font-family:Tahoma; font-size:10pt">. </span></p><p style="font-size:10pt; line-height:115%; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 21.3pt; text-indent:-21.3pt"><span style="font-family:Tahoma; font-size:10pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="font-size:10pt; line-height:115%; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 21.3pt; text-indent:-21.3pt"><span style="font-family:Tahoma; font-size:10pt">2.5</span><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'">&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; </span><span style="font-family:Tahoma; font-size:10pt">Variations between minimum and “gold” standards amongst offshore helicopter operators are a source of concern in the specific area</span><span style="font-family:Tahoma; font-size:10pt">s</span><span style="font-family:Tahoma; font-size:10pt"> of pilot training</span><span style="font-family:Tahoma; font-size:10pt"> and operating procedures</span><span style="font-family:Tahoma; font-size:10pt">. Bond and CHC, for example, only train their pilots to the</span><span style="font-family:Tahoma; font-size:10pt"> minimum standard and industry sources tell RMT that this is because the companies are under no statutory obligation to achieve higher standards in this and other</span><span style="font-family:Tahoma; font-size:10pt"> areas, so this extra cost is avoided. In our view, Norwegian standards should be adopted acro</span><span style="font-family:Tahoma; font-size:10pt">ss the industry and this standardisation should be set in law.</span></p><p style="font-size:10pt; line-height:115%; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 21.3pt; text-indent:-21.3pt"><span style="font-family:Tahoma; font-size:10pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="font-size:10pt; line-height:115%; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 21.3pt; text-indent:-21.3pt"><span style="font-family:Tahoma; font-size:10pt">2.6</span><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'">&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; </span><span style="font-family:Tahoma; font-size:10pt">Historically, helicopter transport in the Norwegian sector of the North Sea was not as safe as that provided for their offshore colleagues in the UK. Between 1966 and 1989 the fatality rate wa</span><span style="font-family:Tahoma; font-size:10pt">s 4.1 for the Norwegian sector and 3.7 for the UK sector per million person flight hours. This difference continued over the 1990s with a fatality rate of</span><span style="font-family:Tahoma; font-size:10pt"> </span><span style="font-family:Tahoma; font-size:10pt">1.6 in the UK compared to 2.3 in the Norwegian sector between 1990 and 1998. </span></p><p style="font-size:10pt; line-height:115%; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 21.3pt; text-indent:-21.3pt"><span style="font-family:Tahoma; font-size:10pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="font-size:10pt; line-height:115%; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 21.3pt; text-indent:-21.3pt"><span style="font-family:Tahoma; font-size:10pt">2.7</span><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'">&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; </span><span style="font-family:Tahoma; font-size:10pt">In the decade between </span><span style="font-family:Tahoma; font-size:10pt">1999 and 2009, however, there were no fatal accidents in the Norwegian sector (a nil rate) whilst the UK’s fatality rate shot up to 5.6 – a deeply worrying reversal of the historic, downward trend across the North Sea. Furthermore, 11 out of the 12 helicop</span><span style="font-family:Tahoma; font-size:10pt">ter accidents in the North Sea between 2001 and 2009 were in the UK sector.</span></p><p style="font-size:10pt; line-height:115%; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 21.3pt; text-indent:-21.3pt"><span style="font-family:Tahoma; font-size:10pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="font-size:10pt; line-height:115%; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 21.3pt; text-indent:-21.3pt"><span style="font-family:Tahoma; font-size:10pt">2.8</span><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'">&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; </span><span style="font-family:Tahoma; font-size:10pt">The Norwegian sector has a different inspection regime and different regulations applying to helicopters and helicopter flights in the North Sea. All of these have been introduced over the last 12 years or so and explain the marked improvement in the safet</span><span style="font-family:Tahoma; font-size:10pt">y record. </span></p><p style="font-size:10pt; line-height:115%; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 21.3pt; text-indent:-21.3pt"><span style="font-family:Tahoma; font-size:10pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="font-size:10pt; line-height:115%; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 21.3pt; text-indent:-21.3pt"><span style="font-family:Tahoma; font-size:10pt">2.9</span><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'">&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; </span><span style="font-family:Tahoma; font-size:10pt">RMT welcome the C</span><span style="font-family:Tahoma; font-size:10pt">ivil </span><span style="font-family:Tahoma; font-size:10pt">A</span><span style="font-family:Tahoma; font-size:10pt">viation </span><span style="font-family:Tahoma; font-size:10pt">A</span><span style="font-family:Tahoma; font-size:10pt">uthority</span><span style="font-family:Tahoma; font-size:10pt">’s announcement on 24</span><span style="font-family:Tahoma; font-size:6.67pt; vertical-align:super">th</span><span style="font-family:Tahoma; font-size:10pt"> September </span><span style="font-family:Tahoma; font-size:10pt">of the review of helicopter operations in the North Sea. We note that t</span><span style="font-family:Tahoma; font-size:10pt">his will involve work with the h</span><span style="font-family:Tahoma; font-size:10pt">ead of helicopter operations at the Norwegian CAA</span><span style="font-family:Tahoma; font-size:10pt"> (as well as officials from the European Aviation Safety Agency)</span><span style="font-family:Tahoma; font-size:10pt">, comparing the record of helicopter operations in the UK and Norwegian sectors of the North Sea. </span><span style="font-family:Tahoma; font-size:10pt">We await with interest</span><span style="font-family:Tahoma; font-size:10pt"> the publication of the CAA’s recommendations in early 2014.</span></p><p style="font-size:10pt; line-height:115%; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 21.3pt; text-indent:-21.3pt"><span style="font-family:Tahoma; font-size:10pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="font-size:10pt; line-height:115%; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 21.3pt; text-indent:-21.3pt"><span style="font-family:Tahoma; font-size:10pt">2.10</span><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'"> </span><span style="font-family:Tahoma; font-size:10pt">RMT also s</span><span style="font-family:Tahoma; font-size:10pt">upport the introduction of a system of guaranteed access to seats for trade union officials on helicopters travelling to and from offshore installations. Not only would this </span><span style="font-family:Tahoma; font-size:10pt">remove a significant barrier to improving </span><span style="font-family:Tahoma; font-size:10pt">the</span><span style="font-family:Tahoma; font-size:10pt"> health and safety culture offshore, </span><span style="font-family:Tahoma; font-size:10pt">it would also provide offshore workers with greater awareness of their workplace rights, as well as benefiting the performance of helicopter operations in the North Sea which is in the interests of all concerned.</span><span style="font-family:Tahoma; font-size:10pt"> </span></p><p style="font-size:10pt; line-height:115%; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 36pt"><span style="font-family:Tahoma; font-size:10pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="font-size:10pt; line-height:115%; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 21.3pt; text-indent:-21.3pt"><span style="font-family:Tahoma; font-size:10pt">2.11</span><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'"> </span><span style="font-family:Tahoma; font-size:10pt">Following the fatal incident on 23</span><span style="font-family:Tahoma; font-size:6.67pt; vertical-align:super">rd</span><span style="font-family:Tahoma; font-size:10pt"> Augu</span><span style="font-family:Tahoma; font-size:10pt">st, the RMT met with industry representatives to discuss a number of issues, including regular trade union access to offshore workers at heliports and on installations</span><span style="font-family:Tahoma; font-size:10pt"> with some positive progress being made</span><a name="_ftnref3"></a><a href="#_ftn3">[3]</a><span style="font-family:Tahoma; font-size:10pt">. S</span><span style="font-family:Tahoma; font-size:10pt">ome </span><span style="font-family:Tahoma; font-size:10pt">subsequent progress has been made in terms</span><span style="font-family:Tahoma; font-size:10pt"> of </span><span style="font-family:Tahoma; font-size:10pt">access to the workforce at </span><span style="font-family:Tahoma; font-size:10pt">but</span><span style="font-family:Tahoma; font-size:10pt"> progress on trade union access to offshore workers in their place of work (i.e. on installations in the North Sea) has slowed. RMT support amendment to the existing law, if necessary, to ensure that </span><span style="font-family:Tahoma; font-size:10pt">offshore workers have </span><span style="font-family:Tahoma; font-size:10pt">regular access to their trade union representatives when they are working on installations</span><span style="font-family:Tahoma; font-size:10pt"> which can be</span><span style="font-family:Tahoma; font-size:10pt"> for period</span><span style="font-family:Tahoma; font-size:10pt">s</span><span style="font-family:Tahoma; font-size:10pt"> of up to three weeks at a time</span><span style="font-family:Tahoma; font-size:10pt">.</span></p><p style="font-size:10pt; line-height:115%; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 21.3pt; text-indent:-21.3pt"><span style="font-family:Tahoma; font-size:10pt">&#xa0;</span></p><ol start="3" type="1" style="margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt"><li style="font-family:Tahoma; font-size:10pt; font-weight:bold; line-height:115%; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 14.49pt; padding-left:6.81pt; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:Tahoma; font-size:10pt; font-weight:bold">Role of domestic regulator</span></li></ol><p style="font-size:10pt; line-height:115%; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 21.3pt; text-indent:-21.3pt"><span style="font-family:Tahoma; font-size:10pt; font-weight:bold">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="font-size:10pt; line-height:115%; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 21.3pt; text-indent:-21.3pt"><span style="font-family:Tahoma; font-size:10pt; font-weight:normal">3.1</span><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'">&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; </span><span style="font-family:Tahoma; font-size:10pt">The role and effectiveness of the Civil Aviation Authority (CAA) </span><span style="font-family:Tahoma; font-size:10pt">is at risk </span><span style="font-family:Tahoma; font-size:10pt">from two recent developments. Firstly, we believe that proposals</span><a name="_ftnref4"></a><a href="#_ftn4">[4]</a><span style="font-family:Tahoma; font-size:10pt"> to extend the regulatory remit of the </span><span style="font-family:Tahoma; font-size:10pt">E</span><span style="font-family:Tahoma; font-size:10pt">uropean </span><span style="font-family:Tahoma; font-size:10pt">A</span><span style="font-family:Tahoma; font-size:10pt">viation </span><span style="font-family:Tahoma; font-size:10pt">S</span><span style="font-family:Tahoma; font-size:10pt">afety </span><span style="font-family:Tahoma; font-size:10pt">A</span><span style="font-family:Tahoma; font-size:10pt">gency (EASA)</span><span style="font-family:Tahoma; font-size:10pt"> </span><span style="font-family:Tahoma; font-size:10pt">to cover helicopter operations in the UK continental shelf will dangerously undermine the responsiveness and loca</span><span style="font-family:Tahoma; font-size:10pt">l knowledge of the UK offshore sector that the CAA has built up over a number of years</span><span style="font-family:Tahoma; font-size:10pt">. </span><span style="font-family:Tahoma; font-size:10pt">RMT argue that member states with extensive helicopter operations central to the transport of workers in an industry should retain the powers to regulate that sector. </span></p><p style="font-size:10pt; line-height:115%; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 21.3pt; text-indent:-21.3pt"><span style="font-family:Tahoma; font-size:10pt; font-weight:bold">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="font-size:10pt; line-height:115%; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 21.3pt; text-indent:-21.3pt"><span style="font-family:Tahoma; font-size:10pt; font-weight:normal">3.2</span><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'">&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; </span><span style="font-family:Tahoma; font-size:10pt">Secondly, the Coalition Government’s decision to</span><span style="font-family:Tahoma; font-size:10pt"> </span><span style="font-family:Tahoma; font-size:10pt">cut</span><span style="font-family:Tahoma; font-size:10pt"> 120 posts </span><span style="font-family:Tahoma; font-size:10pt">at the CAA is a serious threat to effective enforcement of the regulatory framework and, therefore, increases the risk to offshore workers obliged to use helicopter transport because transport</span><span style="font-family:Tahoma; font-size:10pt"> by sea takes too long. </span></p><p style="font-size:10pt; line-height:115%; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 21.3pt; text-indent:-21.3pt"><span style="font-family:Tahoma; font-size:10pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="font-size:10pt; line-height:115%; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 21.3pt; text-indent:-21.3pt"><span style="font-family:Tahoma; font-size:10pt; font-weight:normal">3.3</span><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'">&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; </span><span style="font-family:Tahoma; font-size:10pt">This is not to say, however, that there are no complaints about or concerns over the CAA’s regulatory performance. For example, the CAA’s response to the fatal incident off the coast of Shetland on 23</span><span style="font-family:Tahoma; font-size:6.67pt; vertical-align:super">rd</span><span style="font-family:Tahoma; font-size:10pt"> August was not widely regar</span><span style="font-family:Tahoma; font-size:10pt">ded as sufficiently strong to prevent a further decline in confidence of offshore workers in this mode of transport or the Super Puma models.</span></p><p style="font-size:10pt; line-height:115%; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 21.3pt; text-indent:-21.3pt"><span style="font-family:Tahoma; font-size:10pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="font-size:10pt; line-height:115%; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 21.3pt; text-indent:-21.3pt"><span style="font-family:Tahoma; font-size:10pt; font-weight:normal">3.4</span><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'">&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; </span><span style="font-family:Tahoma; font-size:10pt">It is also worrying that the CAA </span><span style="font-family:Tahoma; font-size:10pt">have only limited powers of enforcement on </span><span style="font-family:Tahoma; font-size:10pt">helicopters</span><span style="font-family:Tahoma; font-size:10pt"> operating within the UK, </span><span style="font-family:Tahoma; font-size:10pt">but registered elsewhere.</span><span style="font-family:Tahoma; font-size:10pt"> Clarity needs to be established in this area and we would prefer those regulatory standards to be brought up to a high level, rather than down to a lower level which is a potential consequence of EASA’s regulatory power grab.</span></p><p style="font-size:10pt; line-height:115%; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 21.3pt; text-indent:-21.3pt"><span style="font-family:Tahoma; font-size:10pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="font-size:10pt; line-height:115%; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 21.3pt; text-indent:-21.3pt"><span style="font-family:Tahoma; font-size:10pt; font-weight:normal">3.5</span><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'">&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; </span><span style="font-family:Tahoma; font-size:10pt">In </span><span style="font-family:Tahoma; font-size:10pt">our view, the Government should take its cue from the H</span><span style="font-family:Tahoma; font-size:10pt">elicopter Safety Steering Group (HSSG)</span><span style="font-family:Tahoma; font-size:10pt"> on which the offshore trade unions, Health and Safety Executive, </span><span style="font-family:Tahoma; font-size:10pt">CAA, </span><span style="font-family:Tahoma; font-size:10pt">oil and gas industry representatives and helicopter operators sit, before taking any decisio</span><span style="font-family:Tahoma; font-size:10pt">ns that affect the regulations applying to helicopter operators in the offshore sector.</span></p><p style="font-size:10pt; line-height:115%; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 21.3pt; text-indent:-21.3pt"><span style="font-family:Tahoma; font-size:10pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="font-size:10pt; line-height:115%; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 21.3pt; text-indent:-21.3pt"><span style="font-family:Tahoma; font-size:10pt; font-weight:normal">3.6</span><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'">&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; </span><span style="font-family:Tahoma; font-size:10pt">Furthermore, in order to regain the confidence of the offshore workforce in helicopter transport, any decisions that the Government makes on the future regulatory fram</span><span style="font-family:Tahoma; font-size:10pt">ework applied to offshore helicopter operations should be consulted on with workers and their trade union representatives,</span><span style="font-family:Tahoma; font-size:10pt"> at the very least.</span></p><p style="font-size:10pt; line-height:115%; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 21.3pt; text-indent:-21.3pt"><span style="font-family:Tahoma; font-size:10pt; font-weight:bold">&#xa0;</span></p><ol start="4" type="1" style="margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt"><li style="font-family:Tahoma; font-size:10pt; font-weight:bold; line-height:115%; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 14.49pt; padding-left:6.81pt; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:Tahoma; font-size:10pt; font-weight:bold">Helicopter fleet statistics</span></li></ol><p style="font-size:10pt; line-height:115%; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 21.3pt; text-indent:-21.3pt"><span style="font-family:Tahoma; font-size:10pt; font-weight:bold">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="font-size:10pt; line-height:115%; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 21.3pt; text-indent:-21.3pt"><span style="font-family:Tahoma; font-size:10pt">4.1 </span><span style="font-family:Tahoma; font-size:10pt">              </span><span style="font-family:Tahoma; font-size:10pt">We are also concerned at the reliability of the Department for Transport’s </span><span style="font-family:Tahoma; font-size:10pt">statistics on the offshore helicopter fleet, including the range of helicopter models used to transport offshore</span><span style="font-family:Tahoma; font-size:10pt"> workers. Our concern has been </span><span style="font-family:Tahoma; font-size:10pt">caused by a recent written answer</span><a name="_ftnref5"></a><a href="#_ftn5">[5]</a><span style="font-family:Tahoma; font-size:10pt"> to a question from Grahame Morris MP requesting information on the composition</span><span style="font-family:Tahoma; font-size:10pt"> of the offshore helicopter fleet. I</span><span style="font-family:Tahoma; font-size:10pt">ncredibly, the Super Puma EC225 and</span><span style="font-family:Tahoma; font-size:10pt"> AS332 L1</span><span style="font-family:Tahoma; font-size:10pt"> </span><span style="font-family:Tahoma; font-size:10pt">models were not included in the Government’s answer.</span></p><p style="font-size:10pt; line-height:115%; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 21.3pt; text-indent:-21.3pt"><span style="font-family:Tahoma; font-size:10pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="font-size:10pt; line-height:115%; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 21.3pt; text-indent:-21.3pt"><span style="font-family:Tahoma; font-size:10pt">4.2 </span><span style="font-family:Tahoma; font-size:10pt">Super Puma models AS332 L, L1, L2 and EC225 account for 60% of the helicopter fleet currently transporting the vast m</span><span style="font-family:Tahoma; font-size:10pt">ajority of the 30,000 strong workforce employed in the UK offshore oil and gas industry. That is 45 out of a fleet of 75</span><span style="font-family:Tahoma; font-size:10pt"> which has clocked up millions of flight hours and passengers </span><span style="font-family:Tahoma; font-size:10pt">over the last ten years alone</span><span style="font-family:Tahoma; font-size:10pt">. </span><span style="font-family:Tahoma; font-size:10pt">T</span><span style="font-family:Tahoma; font-size:10pt">rade unions on the H</span><span style="font-family:Tahoma; font-size:10pt">elicopter Safety </span><span style="font-family:Tahoma; font-size:10pt">S</span><span style="font-family:Tahoma; font-size:10pt">teer</span><span style="font-family:Tahoma; font-size:10pt">ing </span><span style="font-family:Tahoma; font-size:10pt">G</span><span style="font-family:Tahoma; font-size:10pt">roup</span><span style="font-family:Tahoma; font-size:10pt"> agreed with the operators’ decision to ground Super Puma models following </span><span style="font-family:Tahoma; font-size:10pt">the fatal incident on 23</span><span style="font-family:Tahoma; font-size:6.67pt; vertical-align:super">rd</span><span style="font-family:Tahoma; font-size:10pt"> August 2013.</span></p><p style="font-size:10pt; line-height:115%; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 21.3pt; text-indent:-21.3pt"><span style="font-family:Tahoma; font-size:10pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="font-size:10pt; line-height:115%; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 21.3pt; text-indent:-21.3pt"><span style="font-family:Tahoma; font-size:10pt">4.3 </span><span style="font-family:Tahoma; font-size:10pt">The EC225 model was taken out of service following two non-fatal emergency ditchings in the North Sea in May and October 2012. </span><span style="font-family:Tahoma; font-size:10pt">It had only been returned to service in the offshore sector a matter of weeks before the fatal accident on 23</span><span style="font-family:Tahoma; font-size:6.67pt; vertical-align:super">rd</span><span style="font-family:Tahoma; font-size:10pt"> August 2013 involving a Super Puma AS332 L2.</span></p><p style="font-size:10pt; line-height:115%; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 21.3pt; text-indent:-21.3pt"><span style="font-family:Tahoma; font-size:10pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="font-size:10pt; line-height:115%; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 21.3pt; text-indent:-21.3pt"><span style="font-family:Tahoma; font-size:10pt">4.4 </span><span style="font-family:Tahoma; font-size:10pt">Two events prior to the 23</span><span style="font-family:Tahoma; font-size:6.67pt; vertical-align:super">rd</span><span style="font-family:Tahoma; font-size:10pt"> August incident are </span><span style="font-family:Tahoma; font-size:10pt">vital to consider in the context of offshore</span><span style="font-family:Tahoma; font-size:10pt"> </span><span style="font-family:Tahoma; font-size:10pt">workers’ </span><span style="font-family:Tahoma; font-size:10pt">confidence in the safety of helicopter transport in the North Sea. Firstly, a survey of 1,600 offshore workers in May 2013 by the Step Change in Safety body, a coalition of the safety regulator HSE, the 5 trade unions and the oil and gas industry,</span><span style="font-family:Tahoma; font-size:10pt"> found that nearly 9 in 10 (86%) of offshore workers did not trust the EC225 model. It was clear from this that trust in helicopter transport in general had declined significantly amongst the offshore workforce, before the fatal accident on 23</span><span style="font-family:Tahoma; font-size:6.67pt; vertical-align:super">rd</span><span style="font-family:Tahoma; font-size:10pt"> August. As</span><span style="font-family:Tahoma; font-size:10pt"> the Step Change in Safety official Les Linklater commented in industry press coverage of the May survey’s finding: “</span><span style="font-family:Tahoma; font-size:10pt">We cannot think of this as an EC225 issue...The EC225 will come back and will be safe to fly again, but there are other airframes out there</span><span style="font-family:Tahoma; font-size:10pt"> and there are confidence issues.”</span><a name="_ftnref6"></a><a href="#_ftn6">[6]</a></p><p style="font-size:10pt; line-height:115%; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 21.3pt; text-indent:-21.3pt"><span style="font-family:Tahoma; font-size:10pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="font-size:10pt; line-height:115%; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 21.3pt; text-indent:-21.3pt"><span style="font-family:Tahoma; font-size:10pt">4.5 </span><span style="font-family:Tahoma; font-size:10pt">Secondly, the reported comments</span><a name="_ftnref7"></a><a href="#_ftn7">[7]</a><span style="font-family:Tahoma; font-size:10pt"> of a helicopter company (CHC) employee in response to an offshore worker’s concern over the safety of the EC225s has served to anger offshore workers and highlight a culture of macho bullying that exists with the tacit acceptance of the employers. Again t</span><span style="font-family:Tahoma; font-size:10pt">his episode occurred before the accident on 23</span><span style="font-family:Tahoma; font-size:6.67pt; vertical-align:super">rd</span><span style="font-family:Tahoma; font-size:10pt"> August, but also serves to highlight the problems over confidence in helicopter transportation that are ingrained in the workforce in the offshore sector.</span></p><p style="font-size:10pt; line-height:115%; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 21.3pt; text-indent:-21.3pt"><span style="font-family:Tahoma; font-size:10pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="font-size:10pt; line-height:115%; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 21.3pt; text-indent:-21.3pt"><span style="font-family:Tahoma; font-size:10pt">4.6 </span><span style="font-family:Tahoma; font-size:10pt">It should also be noted that the “Boots On” cam</span><span style="font-family:Tahoma; font-size:10pt">paign to reassure and support offshore workers was agreed and launched by</span><span style="font-family:Tahoma; font-size:10pt"> members of</span><span style="font-family:Tahoma; font-size:10pt"> the HSSG, in response to the </span><span style="font-family:Tahoma; font-size:10pt">further concern over </span><span style="font-family:Tahoma; font-size:10pt">helicopter safety raised by the fatal incident on 23</span><span style="font-family:Tahoma; font-size:6.67pt; vertical-align:super">rd</span><span style="font-family:Tahoma; font-size:10pt"> August. RMT believe that this unified approach is the most effecti</span><span style="font-family:Tahoma; font-size:10pt">ve way of improving the health and safety of all offshore workers, on installations and on the helicopters used to transfer them to and from the workplace.</span></p><p style="font-size:10pt; line-height:115%; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 21.3pt; text-indent:-21.3pt"><span style="font-family:Tahoma; font-size:10pt">&#xa0;</span></p><ol start="5" type="1" style="margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt"><li style="font-family:Tahoma; font-size:10pt; font-weight:bold; line-height:115%; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 14.49pt; padding-left:6.81pt; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:Tahoma; font-size:10pt; font-weight:bold">Access to justice </span></li></ol><p style="font-size:10pt; line-height:115%; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 21.3pt; text-indent:-21.3pt"><span style="font-family:Tahoma; font-size:10pt; font-weight:bold">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="font-size:10pt; line-height:115%; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 21.3pt; text-indent:-21.3pt"><span style="font-family:Tahoma; font-size:10pt">5.1 </span><span style="font-family:Tahoma; font-size:10pt">The RMT supports Patricia Ferguson MSP’s </span><span style="font-family:Tahoma; font-size:10pt; font-style:italic">Inquiries into Deaths (Scotland) B</span><span style="font-family:Tahoma; font-size:10pt; font-style:italic">ill </span><span style="font-family:Tahoma; font-size:10pt">and would urge </span><span style="font-family:Tahoma; font-size:10pt">Transcom to consider</span><span style="font-family:Tahoma; font-size:10pt"> apply</span><span style="font-family:Tahoma; font-size:10pt">ing</span><span style="font-family:Tahoma; font-size:10pt"> pressure on the Scottish Government, via the Scotland Office, HSE and CAA to support this Bill which contains much needed reform to the fatal accident inquiry process in Scotland that attends such tragic acc</span><span style="font-family:Tahoma; font-size:10pt">idents. </span><span style="font-family:Tahoma; font-size:10pt">The consultation on the Bill is open to responses until 31</span><span style="font-family:Tahoma; font-size:6.67pt; vertical-align:super">st</span><span style="font-family:Tahoma; font-size:10pt"> January 2014</span><a name="_ftnref8"></a><a href="#_ftn8">[8]</a><span style="font-family:Tahoma; font-size:10pt">. </span><span style="font-family:Tahoma; font-size:10pt">Whilst all effort must be expended in protecting the lives and well being of offshore workers in the North Sea, they must also be assured that access to justice will be swi</span><span style="font-family:Tahoma; font-size:10pt">ft, straightforward and effective should </span><span style="font-family:Tahoma; font-size:10pt">the worst case scenario be realised</span><span style="font-family:Tahoma; font-size:10pt">.</span></p><p style="font-size:10pt; line-height:115%; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 21.3pt; text-indent:-21.3pt"><span style="font-family:Tahoma; font-size:10pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="font-size:10pt; line-height:115%; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 21.3pt; text-indent:-21.3pt"><span style="font-family:Tahoma; font-size:10pt">5.2 To further illustrate the need for reform in this area, we point to </span><span style="font-family:Tahoma; font-size:10pt">the </span><span style="font-family:Tahoma; font-size:10pt">unacceptable </span><span style="font-family:Tahoma; font-size:10pt">experiences of the families of the 14 offshore workers and 2</span><span style="font-family:Tahoma; font-size:10pt"> air</span><span style="font-family:Tahoma; font-size:10pt"> crew who died on 1</span><span style="font-family:Tahoma; font-size:6.67pt; vertical-align:super">st</span><span style="font-family:Tahoma; font-size:10pt"> April 2009 in an incident north east of Peterhead involving a Super Puma AS332 L2, the same helicopter model involved in the 23</span><span style="font-family:Tahoma; font-size:6.67pt; vertical-align:super">rd</span><span style="font-family:Tahoma; font-size:10pt"> August </span><span style="font-family:Tahoma; font-size:10pt">incident. The families of those who died in April 2009 are still waiting for the Procurator Fiscal to open the Fatal A</span><span style="font-family:Tahoma; font-size:10pt">ccident Inquiry into this tragic episode. Whilst that inquiry will finally commence on 6</span><span style="font-family:Tahoma; font-size:6.67pt; vertical-align:super">th</span><span style="font-family:Tahoma; font-size:10pt"> January 2014, a preliminary hearing </span><span style="font-family:Tahoma; font-size:10pt">in November</span><span style="font-family:Tahoma; font-size:10pt"> was cancelled at the last minute, leaving the bereaved relatives who had travelled to Aberdeen from all over the UK s</span><span style="font-family:Tahoma; font-size:10pt">everely inconvenienced and again asking why such a significant inquiry into the death of their loved ones should be subject to constant delay and its terms of reference, powers and scope, so severely </span><span style="font-family:Tahoma; font-size:10pt">restricte</span><span style="font-family:Tahoma; font-size:10pt">d.</span></p><p style="font-size:10pt; line-height:115%; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 21.3pt; text-indent:-21.3pt"><span style="font-family:Tahoma; font-size:10pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="font-size:10pt; line-height:115%; margin:0pt 0pt 10pt 21.3pt; text-indent:-21.3pt"><span style="font-family:Tahoma; font-size:10pt; font-style:italic">December 2013</span><a name="_GoBack"></a></p><p style="margin:0pt; text-align:center"><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:10pt">6</span></p><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:10pt">&#xa0;</span></p></div><hr style="width:33%; height:1px; text-align:left" /><p style="margin:0pt"><a name="_ftn1"></a><a href="#_ftnref1">[1]</a><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:10pt"> Quoted at </span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:10pt">3.2 </span><a href="http://www.scotland.gov.uk/Publications/2013/07/5746/3"><span style="color:#0000ff; font-family:Calibri; font-size:10pt; text-decoration:underline">http://www.scotland.gov.uk/Publications/2013/07/5746/3</span></a><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:10pt"> </span></p><p style="margin:0pt"><a name="_ftn2"></a><a href="#_ftnref2">[2]</a><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:10pt"> </span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:10pt; font-style:italic">Hansard </span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:10pt">27</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:6.67pt; vertical-align:super">th</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:10pt"> November 2013, Col 127</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:10pt">WH</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:10pt">.</span></p><p style="margin:0pt"><a name="_ftn3"></a><a href="#_ftnref3">[3]</a><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:10pt"> </span><a href="http://www.itfglobal.org/news-online/index.cfm/newsdetail/9430"><span style="color:#0000ff; font-family:Calibri; font-size:10pt; text-decoration:underline">http://www.itfglobal.org/news-online/index.cfm/newsdetail/9430</span></a><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:10pt"> </span></p><p style="margin:0pt"><a name="_ftn4"></a><a href="#_ftnref4">[4]</a><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:10pt"> </span><a href="http://www.easa.europa.eu/rulemaking/docs/npa/2013/NPA%202013-10.pdf"><span style="color:#0000ff; font-family:Calibri; font-size:10pt; text-decoration:underline">http://www.easa.europa.eu/rulemaking/docs/npa/2013/NPA%202013-10.pdf</span></a><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:10pt"> </span></p><p style="margin:0pt"><a name="_ftn5"></a><a href="#_ftnref5">[5]</a><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:10pt"> </span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:10pt; font-style:italic">Hansard </span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:10pt">2</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:6.67pt; vertical-align:super">nd</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:10pt"> December 2013 col. 506W</span></p><p style="margin:0pt"><a name="_ftn6"></a><a href="#_ftnref6">[6]</a><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:10pt"> </span><a href="http://www.energyvoice.com/2013/06/nine-in-10-oil-workers-dont-trust-ec225s-after-ditchings-survey-finds/"><span style="color:#0000ff; font-family:Calibri; font-size:10pt; text-decoration:underline">http://www.energyvoice.c</span><span style="color:#0000ff; font-family:Calibri; font-size:10pt; text-decoration:underline">om/2013/06/nine-in-10-oil-workers-dont-trust-ec225s-after-ditchings-survey-finds/</span></a><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:10pt"> </span></p><p style="margin:0pt"><a name="_ftn7"></a><a href="#_ftnref7">[7]</a><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:10pt"> </span><a href="http://www.telegraph.co.uk/news/uknews/scotland/10268574/Helicopter-crash-workers-told-to-put-big-boy-pants-on-after-expressing-safety-fears.html"><span style="color:#0000ff; font-family:Calibri; font-size:10pt; text-decoration:underline">http://ww</span><span style="color:#0000ff; font-family:Calibri; font-size:10pt; text-decoration:underline">w.telegraph.co.uk/news/uknews/scotland/10268574/Helicopter-crash-workers-told-to-put-big-boy-pants-on-after-expressing-safety-fears.html</span></a><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:10pt"> </span></p><p style="margin:0pt"><a name="_ftn8"></a><a href="#_ftnref8">[8]</a><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:10pt"> </span><a href="http://www.scottish.parliament.uk/gettinginvolved/66152.aspx"><span style="color:#0000ff; font-family:Calibri; font-size:10pt; text-decoration:underline">http://www.scottish.parliament.uk/getti</span><span style="color:#0000ff; font-family:Calibri; font-size:10pt; text-decoration:underline">nginvolved/66152.aspx</span></a><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:10pt"> </